Leader in the development and publishing of mobile games, Gameloft® has established itself as one of the top innovators in its field since 2000. 

Gameloft creates games for all digital platforms, two of which are featured in the “Top 10 Games by All-Time Worldwide Downloads” from App Annie. Gameloft operates its own established franchises such as Asphalt®, Order & Chaos, Modern Combat and Dungeon Hunter and also partners with major rights holders including Universal, Illumination Entertainment, Disney®, Marvel®, Hasbro®, Fox Digital Entertainment, Mattel® and Ferrari®. 

Gameloft distributes its games in over 100 countries andemploys 4,600 people worldwide. Every month, 114 million unique users can be reached by advertisers in Gameloft games with Gameloft Advertising Solutions, a leading B2B offering dedicated to brands and agencies. Gameloft is a Vivendi company.

All trademarks referenced above are owned by their respective trademark owners.

Job Description
Casual and Hyper casual gaming has seen unprecedented growth over the past years. While enforcing the expertise in our core gaming business, Gameloft doesn’t stay still, and has been moving swiftly with the trends. Gameloft Vietnam studios are trusted to develop these activities and are looking for talented Senior Game Designers to enforce and build our creation capacity.



Job holders will be part of our core team, and exert the following main responsibilities:

Creating design documents which defines the blueprint for the entire game, from the  gameplay, the level design,… to the on boarding experience and the interface;
Designing the mechanisms, the rules of the games, making sure that everything is balanced wisely;
Creating levels, missions, and other game aspects to create the best gaming experience to players, with an creative, immersive and addictive game play;
Writing the game’s story line, menu text and narrative (if any);
Following the full game development cycle to make sure the game design is fulfilled at expected quality and following the agreed planning;
Providing proper support and guidance to other Game Designers to complete all ongoing and future prototypes/projects; organizing market updates, game reviews, initiatives to boost innovative ideas;
Coaching, training, mentoring the assigned Game Designers to help them perform their assignments successfully, develop skills, driving them to the best commitment, work quality and performance;
Assisting Studio Lead Game Designer and Producers in all related-Game Design matters, within the scope of the assigned projects, or team/department; joining talent recruitment upon request.


Few words about work locations

·         Ho Chi Minh City is the biggest city in the South, the ultra-dynamic capital of the Vietnam’s economy.

